author: Shibani Mahtani
title: Ousted Ruling Party Leader Eyes Comeback in Myanmar Election Maneuvering
text:
PHYU, Myanmar—Ousted in an internal party coup three months ago, the former chairman of Myanmar’s ruling party is campaigning hard to hold on to a legislative seat in elections where he hopes to emerge as an influential figure when his military-allied party jockeys with that of opposition leader Aung San Suu Kyi.
The legislator, Shwe Mann, who has remained speaker of parliament, was deposed as leader of the Union Solidarity and Development Party in a midnight reshuffle in August and replaced by President Thein Sein. He...
